# üçÖ Golang - Pomodoro CLI 

This app is a small CLI that lets you set up a timer to use the pomodoro focus technique.

It consists of multiple focus periods seperated by small breaks used to reflect on the work done during the focus time. After 4 focus periods, a long break is taken to rest.

## Installation

### Source
for this step you should [Download and install Go](https://go.dev/doc/install)

Then,

```bash
git clone https://github.com/AliMarzouk/Golang-PomodoroCLI

// to run on go
go run . 
// or build and run
go build && ./pomodorocli
```

### Run binary 

You can download the latest pre-compiled binary form [github releases tab](https://github.com/AliMarzouk/Golang-PomodoroCLI/releases/latest)

